File: Acting eThekwini Mayor Fawzia. DURBAN - The ANC in KwaZulu-Natal has named current MEC for Transport Mxolisi Kaunda as the eThekwini mayoral candidate. The party briefed the media on proposed mayoral candidates for Msunduzi and eThekwini municipalities on Thursday. READ: Msunduzi executive council asked to step down  Kaunda will take over from Zandile Gumede who was fired as the eThekwini mayor. Gumede is facing fraud and corruption charges relating to a R208-million waste tender. She is out on R50,000 bail and is due back in court in January 2020. Fawzia Peer is currently serving as Acting Mayor of the eThekwini Municipality.